tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE fingerprints (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  fingerprint_data BYTEA
)

CREATE TABLE facial_features (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  face_image BYTEA
)

CREATE TABLE users (
  user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  username VARCHAR(50) UNIQUE,
  password_hash BYTEA
)

CREATE TABLE authentication_logs (
  log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  user_id INT,
  timestamp TIMESTAMP,
  success BOOLEAN
)

CREATE TABLE user_biometrics (
    user_id INT,
    fingerprint_id INT,
    facial_id INT,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (fingerprint_id) REFERENCES fingerprints(id),
    FOREIGN KEY (facial_id) REFERENCES facial_features(id)
);

CREATE TABLE authentication_logs (
    log_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    authentication_time TIMESTAMP,
    success BOOLEAN,
    FOREIGN KEY (user_id) REFERENCES users(user_id)
);
